    <item>
      <title>Does not output Meta Keywords</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/xrowmetadata/forum/general/does_not_output_meta_keywords</link>
      <description>I found, that the sample template (page_head.tpl.sample) will not output the Keywords correctly.&#13;
This used to work fine with ez 4.1, but does not with Community Project 2011.12.&#13;
&#13;
Problem seems to be, that the "Keyword" component now is an array and not a simple string anymore. &#13;
&#13;
I fixed that by adding an implode operator.&#13;
So, i use &#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
{if $meta.keywords}&#13;
     &lt;meta name="keywords" content="{$meta.keywords|implode(', ')|wash}" /&gt;&#13;
{/if}&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
Please also see the next post on the "empy keywords" check by Edi.&#13;
</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Marco Zinn)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/xrowmetadata/forum/general/does_not_output_meta_keywords</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 10 Mar 2012 11:41:58 +0000</pubDate>
    </item>
